  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a user, I want to be able to complete a full sync quickly, so that I can catch up to chain head without state growing larger than the node can catch up. This most often happens in forest mode which is more useful for archive use-cases. \r\n\r\n* New storage format changes may be able to help with full sync on Bonsai #5052 \r\n* Forest - we need to determine what the areas are for performance improvements - some of the bonsai improvements can be tweaked to suit forest use-case (unknown) \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Faster performance and catch up to chain head from Full Sync \r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. Start a full sync \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\n- Quick and reliable sync \r\n- Decent query performance for old blocks\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\nCannot catch up to chain head in many instances with Besu on a full archive node. \r\n",
